mapping(Document, StopWords) - Method in class Index
mapping method takes a Document, for each word in the document (if not in StopList), it will check if it is in the HashMap if it is in the map, it will add the document to its Docs if it is not in the map, it will create a new entry in the map with the word as its key and the Document as its first Document in Docs complexity O(n^2)

S

search(HashMap<String, Docs>, StopWords, String) - Method in class SearchEngine
search method searches through a HashMap with a single-word query or multi-word query (after ignoring words in StopList) single-word query: searches map for key matching query and returns its value Docs set of Documents multi-word query: searches map for keys matching words in query and returns a set of Documents that all contain all the words from query complexity: O(n^2)
